		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>25 August 1850</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phila</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">My Dr Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">I find by one of the Occidents<lb/> recd from you by <persName>Simmonds</persName> that you had returned<lb/> from <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>&#8212;I have not received my pack nor<lb/> the small catechisms wrote for let me ask you to<lb/> look after it. I requested you to subscribe to the<lb/> Asmoneon for me pray let me know if you have<lb/> done os&#44; if inconvenient I will apply to <persName>Mr Isaac&#39;s</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I am glad to find that your Congregation<lb/> is indisposed to lose your valuable &#38; long services<lb/> I trust you will come to an understanding</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Government has made a stir of our having<lb/> a Minister which I think the congregation will be<lb/> obliged to listen to&#59; left to them&#44; their children<lb/> would grow up in complete ignorance&#44; as we have<lb/> no person competent to teach the Hebrew&#44; they have<lb/> gone back sadly since <persName>Mr Nathans</persName> departure&#44; I<lb/> have done all I could to get one&#44; but what can<lb/> one do against a <add>&#63;</add>&#44; the danger to the congregation<lb/> is imminent for already some of the children are<lb/> going to a Christian clergyman&#39;s school while the<lb/> Lutheran&#44; Protestant&#44; &#38; Dutch Reformed Parsons<lb/> have formed a union for distributing <sic>trachs</sic><lb/> which they send from house to house.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>see how exposed we are&#44; all for the sake of a<lb/> few dollars&#8212;<sic>wont</sic> you say something on it&#8212;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I regret to add that my Son <persName>Jacob</persName> arrived<lb/> from <placeName>Panama</placeName> in a deplorable state of illness he<lb/> is a trifling better&#44; but doubt if he will ever<lb/> become a sound man</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">With best wishes I rem Dr Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">yours truly <persName role="author">A Wolff</persName></p>
			<p>the congregation can <sic>will</sic> pay for a minister for<lb/> the members are better off than they were 2 years ago.<lb/> the children have forgotten all that <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> taught&#44;<lb/> nay very few can say <del>then</del> a word of Hebrew &#38; if it continues&#44; the<lb/> <del>lang Hebrew</del> language will be entirely lost&#44; many young men called<lb/> to the law cannot repeat the blessing we are going back<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> to when <persName>Mr Carillon</persName> found us&#8212;the Sunday School<lb/> has also falling off exceedingly only 40 at present of<lb/> which 14 are my nieces nephews &#38; grand children&#44; <add>&#63;</add> as to the<lb/> state of elementary schooling in the poor children it is<lb/> deplorable&#44; nor will any join me in the <sic>expence</sic> of<lb/> instructing them do say something on it&#8212;the congregation<lb/> has no greater opponent than your friend <persName>Simmonds</persName><lb/> whose hatred &#38; malice of me instigates him to oppose<lb/> every thing good that I propose&#44; you will think it</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>strange that he would get others to join him&#44; but he<lb/> does&#44; altho&#39; they condemn his conduct&#8212;so every thing<lb/> is going to the old way&#8212;the Synagogue is badly<lb/> attended&#44; a great many remain away <del>that attended</del><lb/> who used to come when they could hear a Sermon</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I forgot to state that <persName>Simmonds</persName> never proposes<lb/> any thing&#59; if he did &#38; it was good I would not hesitate<lb/> to join him&#59;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The minister of public instruction in<lb/> <placeName>Copenhagen</placeName> has stirred into our affairs thro&#39; <persName>Dr Levison</persName><lb/> second minister of that congregation he is desirous of<lb/> coming here. I have sent in my declaration to Government<lb/> exposing our situation &#38; wants&#8212;which I trust will have<lb/> some weight.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">There was no package for me on board<lb/> the Radius that brought the Occident for <persName>Simmonds</persName></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philada.</placeName></p>
			<p>via <placeName>Balt.</placeName></p>
          
